snippet.title: I tested every myth in Rocket League and learned something INSANE
snippet.description:
You don't know as much about Rocket League as you think you do and I'm going to prove it. Rocket League has tons of myths and I'm going to test them all with @Wayton Pilkin to see if they are real or busted. This led me to find some insane facts about the game that are actually useful! 

If you like this video, check out @Mr-Napkin!

For more info about Myth #5 - https://youtu.be/XoOWKG3xv7U?t=116

Want chances to be in a video? Hop in my discord!
https://discord.gg/striped

Socials:
Twitter: https://twitter.com/Stripedgg
Twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/striped

I'm giving away 60,000 credits at 600k subs so subcribe to be entered!

---
0:00 Intro
0:53 Competitive doesn't average ranks
1:23 Boosting while supersonic is faster
1:56 Scarab is OP
2:50 More people are unsubscribed
3:03 Double reset without air roll
3:33 Close to ranking up = worse tm8s
4:16 Wavedash on another car
4:38 Fall faster with nose down
5:25 Aerial faster by accelerating
5:42 Air rolling makes you faster
6:20 Epic Games has worse servers
6:49 Flip reset on puck
7:47 Small pads give you over 12 boost
8:27 You can choose demo spawn side
9:13 Demo backwards
9:47 GCs can't score open nets
9:57 There's no custom mode where you can't score
10:32 Quick chatting is OP
11:07 Age determines your rank
11:48 You can't win by only goalkeeping
12:21 Pro settings make you better

Co-editor: @Sir Classy

snippet.title: I tried RISKY Kickoff Strategies in Ranked
snippet.description:
Kickoffs are so much more boring in Rocket League than they need to be. So I put a twist on them to make them more interesting. I tried new risky kickoff strategies in ranked Rocket League.

My Links
‚Ä£ Discord: https://discord.gg/32Yp5zb
‚Ä£ Twitter: https://twitter.com/WaytonPilkin
‚Ä£ Twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/wayton
‚Ä£ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/waytonpilkin
‚Ä£ TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@waytonpilkin

Rocket League Kickoffs are one of the most important aspects of the game. It determines who gets play to play offense first which is often a big difference maker in a game's outcome. Right now, everyone in the player base uses the same kickoff strategy in Rocket League. Today, I experimented with some friends to see if we could come up with any strategies that worked better or perfectly countered that standard strategy that everyone uses right now. It was a lot of fun and we actually walked away with something that we'll probably end up using in future ranked games. New Rocket League kickoff strategies are a lot of fun to try out even if they aren't successful.

snippet.title: The Essential Mechanic That Pros REFUSE To Practice
snippet.description:
There is an extremely valuable mechanic in Rocket League that pros know about but still refuse to practice. It's a basic fundamental that is far from being perfected by anyone but they still don't put time into improving it. Today I investigate and analyze exactly why that is.

My Links
‚Ä£ Discord: https://discord.gg/32Yp5zb
‚Ä£ Twitter: https://twitter.com/WaytonPilkin
‚Ä£ Twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/wayton
‚Ä£ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/waytonpilkin
‚Ä£ TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@waytonpilkin

Strength & Accuracy: 6CF3-4C0B-32B4-1AC7
Air Roll Shots: 8D13-FFB7-AC37-7089
Shooting Consistency: 4912-A5C9-9A56-555D
Roller Shots: C197-C7CF-713C-CC2D
Workshop Map: Aim Training by Coco

0:00 Intro
0:39 Professional Opinions
2:08 The Experiment
2:50 Day 1
6:17 Day 2
8:16 Day 3
9:17 The Results

Thanks to @Virge, @Shock, and @Rogue Gyro for taking the time to chat with me! There is no single player in the world that has even come close to mastering shooting in Rocket League. But it turns out, there's a good reason for that. Shooting in Rocket League is one of the most difficult things to practice because it's just so repetitive and, put frankly, boring. However, practicing it clearly does have its upsides. I learned a lot this week from talking with these pros and coaches and experimenting with shooting practice for myself. I'm sure there are barely any people out there that have committed to shooting training in Rocket League as much as I did this week so hopefully you all learn something from this too!
